    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels like we're just dancing around it though. the truth is the candidate only changed their mind because the internal polling showed the old stance was hurting us with moderate voters. if we keep saying it's about \"nuance\" or \"new data\" and a reporter catches us in that lie, it'll be a disaster for our consistency score. shouldn't we just find a way to say the original stance was actually consistent with the new one?",
