      "content": "It can be challenging to spin a complete change in opinion without incurring negative consequences. One possible approach is to reframe the issue in terms of a broader policy agenda, such as whether the current corporate rate is too high or not. By using phrases like \"the candidate has reaffirmed their commitment to a more effective tax system\" or \"they're focusing on finding a solution that works for all stakeholders\", you can imply a consistent direction without explicitly admitting that the earlier stance was incorrect.",
